Ad Text:
Senior Data Scientist

Perth (Hybrid)
Data Science | ML | NLP | GenAI | Data Platforms


The Opportunity

A high-performing technology consultancy is looking to strengthen its advanced analytics and AI capability by bringing in a senior, all-rounder Data Scientist.

This role suits someone who sits comfortably across data science, data platforms and business problem-solving — equally confident building models, working with data engineers, and translating outcomes to stakeholders.

What You’ll Be Doing

Designing and delivering end-to-end data science solutions, from problem definition to production
Building machine learning models (regression, classification, clustering, recommendation systems)
Working on Natural Language Processing use cases (text classification, sentiment analysis, entity extraction)
Applying statistical analysis and predictive modelling to real-world business problems
Productionising models using modern cloud and big data platforms
Collaborating with data engineers on ingestion, modelling and orchestration
Contributing to GenAI initiatives (LLMs, applied AI, agentic workflows)
Communicating insights clearly to both technical and non-technical stakeholders

What They’re Looking For

Essential

Strong experience across data science and applied machine learning
Hands-on background in NLP / text mining
Solid grounding in statistics, predictive modelling and analytics
Experience productionising models in cloud environments
Ability to work across the full lifecycle — data, modelling, deployment and insight
Strongly valued

Experience working alongside data platforms (e.g. Spark-based environments, modern warehouses)
Exposure to Azure ML or similar platforms
SQL proficiency and understanding of data modelling concepts
Comfort operating in consulting or project-based delivery environments
Nice to have

Broader data engineering or BI exposure
GenAI / LLM experience
Research or academic background (PhD or equivalent)
Experience mentoring or guiding other data professionals
 

If this sounds like you, please apply via Seek or email your CV directly to
thana@psgaus.com.au

Data Architect

Perth (Hybrid)
Data Platforms | Architecture | Modelling | GenAI

The Opportunity

A growing technology consultancy is looking for a Data Architect to lead the design of modern, scalable data platforms across complex client environments.

This role is ideal for someone who enjoys owning the technical direction, shaping architecture decisions, and setting standards — while still staying close enough to delivery to ensure designs actually work in practice.


What You’ll Be Doing

Designing end-to-end data architectures across cloud data platforms
Owning and leading data modelling standards (analytical and operational)
Defining ingestion, transformation and orchestration patterns
Providing technical direction across Databricks and Snowflake environments
Partnering with senior stakeholders to translate business needs into architecture
Supporting and guiding delivery teams on complex implementations
Contributing to GenAI architecture patterns and future-state design

What They’re Looking For

Essential

Strong background in data architecture and data modelling
Deep experience with Databricks and/or Snowflake
Proven ability to design scalable, production-grade data platforms
Experience working across multiple client or project environments
Nice to have

Exposure to GenAI / LLM-driven architectures
Broader data engineering or data science background
AWS-native data platforms
Mentorship or technical leadership experience

If this sounds like you, please apply via Seek or email your CV directly to
thana@psgaus.com.au

The Business
MiTek’s Automation business in Australia is one of its fastest-growing and most strategically important divisions, delivering advanced truss and frame manufacturing systems that combine mechanical design, control systems and software-driven automation. Over the past three years, revenue has grown from around $4 million to nearly $30 million, significantly exceeding targets and reflecting strong market demand for MiTek’s integrated automation solutions. The business designs, builds and supports everything from standalone machines to fully automated production lines across greenfield and brownfield sites, backed by a multidisciplinary local engineering team spanning controls, electrical, mechanical and software.
 
This role
Act as the strategic SME for MiTek’s automation portfolio, taking ownership of control systems and electrical standards across the business. This role blends hands-on engineering with forward-looking strategy, requiring a deep understanding of existing machinery to define improvement roadmaps, drive standardisation and lift system performance.
You’ll mentor and technically guide engineers, lead continuous improvement initiatives, and support critical customer site escalations and breakdowns when required. The role is deliberately balanced - approximately 35–40% hands-on delivery, 35–40% strategic planning and improvement, and 20–30% customer site attendance (with higher site engagement during the first three months) - offering genuine technical ownership and influence across MiTek’s automation landscape.
 
Requirements

Bachelor’s degree in Engineering or Computer Science or revenant Trades background (Electrical, Mechatronics, Mechanical, Electronics or similar)
5+ years’ experience in manufacturing or industrial automation
Strong PLC experience with Allen-Bradley/Rockwell/Siemens (essential)
2+ years’ experience programming in C#
Experience with SQL Server / T-SQL
Solid understanding of machine safety, FAT/SAT and commissioning
Strong troubleshooting skills across servos, VSDs, sensors, drives and mechanical systems
Experience reviewing PLC code and mentoring junior engineers
AutoCAD Electrical experience (advantageous)
PILZ CMSE certification (highly regarded)
 
If this is interesting to you, please click apply or reach out to emmao@sde.com.au

At Alex Bank, we’re not like the big banks. We’re a digital-first, customer-focused lender committed to fairness, simplicity, and speed. With a rapidly growing customer base, award-winning digital products, and a culture built on innovation, Alex Bank has been recognised as one of Australia’s fastest-growing companies on both the AFR Fast Starters and Deloitte Fast 50 Technology lists.

About the Role

As a Data Engineer at Alex, you’ll play a pivotal role in shaping the data foundations that power our fully digital, customer centric banking experience. Working within a modern, cloud native environment built on Azure and serverless technologies, you’ll design and deliver data solutions that help us understand our customers deeply and support smarter, fairer financial products.

You’ll collaborate across the business from technology and product to external partners to define requirements, build scalable data models, and implement robust data pipelines that enable analytics, reporting, and data driven insights. Your work will directly influence how we personalise experiences, streamline operations, and continue to challenge traditional banking.

This role is ideal for someone who thrives in a fastmoving, innovative environment. As part of a small, highly skilled team, you’ll have the opportunity to work across a broad range of initiatives, contribute to the evolution of our Integrated Data Platform, and help shape the future of data at Alex. If you’re passionate about modern data engineering, excited by emerging technologies, and motivated by meaningful impact, you’ll feel right at home here.

What You’ll Do

Partner with teams across Alex to understand data needs and translate them into scalable technical solutions
Design, build, and maintain data pipelines, data models, and data stores that support analytics, reporting, and AI initiatives
Contribute to the design and implementation of our Integrated Data Platform, ensuring alignment with governance, regulatory requirements, and strategic priorities
Analyse new and existing data sources to determine their suitability and integration approach
Implement and uphold engineering standards, tools, and best practices to ensure high quality, reliable data solutions
Monitor, support, and optimise scheduled jobs and data workflows
Review your own work and lead peer reviews to maintain engineering excellence
Provide guidance and support to stakeholders to help them use data effectively
Stay across emerging data technologies and trends, offering insights that shape future enhancements
Build strong relationships with internal and external partners, communicating technical concepts clearly and confidently

What You’ll Bring

3–5 years of hands on experience in data engineering, ideally within banking, finance, or other highly regulated environments
A solid understanding of data modelling, data pipelines, data stores, and scheduled job orchestration
Experience designing, developing, deploying, securing, and maintaining data solutions on modern cloud platforms (Azure preferred)
Strong Data Engineering skills (SQL, Python or similar) and familiarity with a range of programming languages applicable to data engineering.
Experience working with Power BI and Databricks while supporting stakeholders in using data effectively
Exposure to Agile delivery practices, CI/CD pipelines, and modern engineering standards
The ability to analyse new and existing data sources and assess their suitability for integration
Strong communication skills, with the ability to explain technical concepts clearly to nontechnical stakeholders
A collaborative mindset and the ability to build strong working relationships across teams
Experience in startup or scaleup environments, or a desire to thrive in a fastmoving, evolving organisation
Extra points for experience with: Temenos / T24; Industry ETL/ELT tools; Remote team collaboration; and, Australian banking or financial services

Why Join Alex Bank

• Join one of Australia’s most innovative and fastest-growing digital banks.

• Competitive remuneration plus performance-based incentives.

• Supportive, collaborative national team with strong values and momentum.

• Access to industry-leading tools, product training, and professional development to support your success.

Ready to Make an Impact?

If you're driven, customer-focused, and ready to play a key role in Alex Bank’s growth in Australia, we’d love to hear from you.

Apply now to join a team that works hard, moves fast, and celebrates success together.

Please note: This role is not open to recruitment agencies.

Want to bring ideas to life?

You're in the right place. If you're looking for a fresh challenge, why choose Aurecon? It comes down to one, crucial question: What kind of world do you want to create for the next generation? Truth is, the decisions being made right now will determine the future of everything - from the local community to the entire planet. One of those decisions is: who do you decide to work for?



How will your ideas contribute to shaping what's next?

Join Aurecon's People Team as our first AI Engineer - a pioneering role dedicated to reimagining how our people experience work. This newly created position is central to transforming HR through AI, helping us deliver smarter, faster, and more human-centric solutions. You'll design, build, and optimise AI-powered tools that streamline recruitment, talent and performance, and career pathways, while enabling data-driven decision-making and supporting Aurecon's People Activation Plan and cultural transformation.

Working at the intersection of technology and human experience, you'll embed AI into core HR workflows and champion responsible innovation. Reporting to the Director of People Enablement, you'll collaborate closely with IT, Digital, and Shared Services to integrate AI into platforms like Workday, Microsoft 365, Copilot, and Teams - making everyday processes simpler, faster, and more engaging for our people.



Here are the key things you will do to 'bring ideas to life':

Design and deploy AI agents and models to automate HR processes such as recruitment, performance reviews, and career pathways.
Integrate AI capabilities into enterprise platforms (Workday, Microsoft Copilot, Teams) to enhance workflows.
Develop and optimise prompts, models, and workflows for use across the People Function.
Champion ethical AI practices, ensuring compliance with Aurecon's governance standards.
Monitor and improve AI performance, retraining models and refining prompts for accuracy and fairness.
Upskill HR leaders and managers to become confident AI users through training and support.
Collaborate in innovation workshops to co-create AI solutions that drive cultural transformation.



What we're looking for:

Proven experience designing and implementing Generative AI solutions.
Proficiency in Python and JavaScript.
Familiarity with Generative AI and agentic frameworks (e.g., LangChain, PydanticAI).
Strong understanding of automation and AI workflow design, with ability to embed AI into enterprise platforms (Workday, Microsoft Copilot, Teams).
Ability to translate complex technical concepts into clear, actionable insights for non-technical stakeholders.
Knowledge of ethical AI principles and responsible innovation practices.
Collaborative mindset with strong communication skills to work across HR, IT, and Digital teams.
Curiosity and adaptability to thrive in a fast-evolving AI landscape and pioneer new solutions.



How will your future be shaped by us?

Joining Aurecon means you'll be at the award-winning edge of innovation and sustainability. AFR ranked us Top 5 among sustainability leaders and Top 3 of all innovative companies in professional services. One Consult awarded us an innovative design award. Plus, we were Consult Australia's large firm of the year.

But this role is more than joining a leading company - it's about being the engineer of Aurecon's AI future. As our first AI Engineer, you'll:

Drive the AI strategy for People Experience - you're not just building models; you're shaping how thousands of employee's experience work.
Drive innovation at scale - your solutions will influence decision-making, automation, and cultural transformation across Aurecon globally.
Be a thought leader - you'll collaborate in design sprints, innovation labs, and workshops,

And because we know the best ideas come from empowered people, you'll have:

Flexible work options - remote work, part-time, and job share arrangements.
Continuous learning - access to AI certifications, leadership programs, and innovation labs to grow your eminence.
Inclusive culture - we've been recognised for gender equality, LGBTI+ inclusion, and have a robust Reconciliation Action Plan.
Wellbeing and lifestyle benefits - competitive paid parental leave, cultural holiday swaps, and wellbeing support programs.




Who is Aurecon?

Aurecon's strength has always been our people. It's our people who build our shared purpose and bring ideas to life. It's our people who imagine and co-create with our clients a better future for people and the planet. Of course, you'll probably know lots of our award-winning projects. The new Allianz Stadium in Sydney? That was us. Tāmaki Regeneration in Auckland? That was us too. And the Tseung Kwan O Interchange in Hong Kong? You guessed it, us. So, when you join us, you'll be joining a community working together to tackle some of the world's most complex challenges.



Ready to bring ideas to life?

Apply now and help lead Aurecon's AI journey. Your background, unique needs and individuality will be valued. Visit our website to learn more at www.aurecongroup.com.

Ad Text:
About the ABC

The ABC is the nation's most trusted and independent source of Australian conversations, culture, and stories. With over 4,000 employees from diverse backgrounds across over 50 locations around Australia and overseas, we are proud to create, curate and deliver high-quality content that informs, educates and entertains Australian communities.

About the Role

This is a great opportunity to design, build and maintain trusted, high-quality data assets that help the ABC unlock the full value of its data. The role enables self-service analytics and supports confident, data-informed decision making across the organisation. Working collaboratively with teams across the ABC, you will combine strong data engineering capability with a passion for transparency, governance and data literacy. You will play a key role in strengthening how data is understood, trusted and used to support ABC’s audiences and strategic goals.

Key Accountabilities

Design, build and maintain integrated, scalable and well-documented data assets using SQL, dbt and best practice data modelling techniques to support self-service analytics.
Establish and maintain robust testing, monitoring and validation frameworks to ensure data accuracy, completeness and reliability.
Under broad direction and in collaboration with internal and external stakeholders, contribute to the design, implementation and support of enterprise data and analytics solutions, including data acquisition, transformation patterns, data models, source-to-target mapping and reporting specifications.
Perform data profiling to understand data quality characteristics, document issues and recommend practical approaches for improvement.
Create clear and accessible documentation for data processes and models, ensuring enterprise data assets are discoverable, understandable and maintainable over time.
Promote and apply data governance best practices to support consistency, security and appropriate use of data across the organisation.
Translate business problems into effective technical data solutions using sound engineering judgement and best practice.

About You

Relevant tertiary qualifications or equivalent practical experience with strong expertise in modern cloud data warehouse technologies such as Snowflake, Google BigQuery, Databricks etc.
Demonstrated experience working with cloud-based data platforms and ecosystems, including data warehouses, ETL tools and data visualisation solutions.
Proven ability to design, develop and maintain complex data models and transformations within a data warehouse environment.
Advanced SQL capability, including building complex transformation logic, supported by experience with version control and collaborative development practices.
Hands-on experience delivering data projects end to end using Agile ways of working and familiarity with scrum delivery approaches.
Strong understanding of data governance practices, including data quality, metadata management, data security, privacy and master data management.
Experience implementing data validation, monitoring and quality management approaches to ensure trusted and reliable data.

For further information on this position please contact Jamie Nedved, Digital Talent Acquisition Lead via email nedved.jamie@abc.net.au 

Full Position Description: Analytics Engineer.pdf

We respectfully request that Recruitment Agencies do not submit applications for this position.

In line with our focus on diversity, applications are strongly encouraged from Indigenous Australians, people from a range of cultural and linguistic backgrounds, people with disability and LGBTIQA+ individuals. The ABC also aims to achieve a gender-balanced workforce

To request recruitment and selection information in alternate formats, request adjustments, or if you have accessibility requirements, please contact accessibility@abc.net.au

For more information on inclusive employee networks within the ABC please refer to Life Page on ABC LinkedIn. 

For more information on working at the ABC visit abc.net.au/careers

Hiring !! - Sr. Process Improvement Specialist

Opportunity to work with Global organization leader in Agentic Ai.
12 months contract - Possibility to extend
Location: Sydney CBD - Hybrid work arrangements
Offering $570/day including super

About the role:

The Senior Process Improvement Specialist will drive operational excellence across our Engineering and Operations divisions. This role is pivotal in aligning our technical workflows with organizational OKRs, ensuring that our Cloud and Data Center operations are scalable, compliant, and highly efficient.

Lead Process Optimization: Design and implement end-to-end processes that improve efficiency and reduce operational risk across engineering and operations.
Drive OKR Alignment: Translate organizational objectives into measurable outcomes; track and report progress using dashboards and KPIs.
Operationalize Change: Support service transitions, release management, and compliance initiatives with structured frameworks and governance.
Enable Data-Driven Decisions: Use analytics to identify bottlenecks, quantify waste, and propose improvements that deliver tangible business value.
Champion Cross-Functional Engagement: Facilitate workshops, manage intake processes, and coordinate dependencies across multiple teams.
Governance & Reporting: Maintain data hygiene, enforce process standards, and ensure audit readiness for regulated environments.
Advance Intelligent Automation: Identify opportunities for AI-driven workflows and implement no-code/low-code solutions to streamline operations and enhance scalability.

Skills for Success (Minimum 5 years relevant experience):

Knowledge of Cloud Infrastructure, Data Center Operations, and process mapping tools like Miro, Lucid charts etc.
Understanding of AI workflow automation, ITIL, ServiceNow, and operational governance.
Experience with no-code/low-code platforms and ability to design and deploy automation solutions.
Ability to identify and implement AI-driven enhancements across business processes.
Proficient in using data analytics for decisions and KPI tracking..
Proficiency in lean methodology and continuous improvement frameworks.
Ability to apply statistical analysis and process optimization techniques.
Experience designing scalable processes in complex or regulated environments.
Ability to lead cross-functional workshops and build stakeholder consensus.
Effective communicator with both technical and non-technical audiences.
Ability to manage organizational change and ensure adoption of new processes.
Skilled in prioritizing initiatives considering impact, risk, and resources.
Strong problem-solving mindset with a focus on reducing operational inefficiencies.

Technical Skills & Qualifications:

Domain Expertise: Minimum 5 years in Process Engineering within Cloud or Data Center operations.
Technical Proficiency: Hands-on experience with ServiceNow, ITIL, and process mapping tools (Miro/Lucid chart/Tableau or any other).
Proven ability to design and deploy automation solutions via no-code/low-code platforms.
Bachelor's degree in a relevant field.
Certifications: Lean Six Sigma (Green/Black Belt), ITIL, or Project Management (PMP/Prince2) preferred.

Please Note: Due to the nature of the role, Candidates will be required to obtain a Federal Government Clearance, based in Sydney and must have unrestricted full work rights to be considered for this role.

Job Title: Senior Data Engineer - Data Intelligence - Data ProductsNew
Ad Text:
Join us on our mission to make a better world of work. 

Culture Amp is the world’s leading employee experience platform, revolutionizing how 25 million employees across more than 6,500 companies create a better world of work. Culture Amp empowers companies of all sizes and industries to transform employee engagement, drive performance management, and develop high-performing teams. Powered by people science and the most comprehensive employee dataset in the world, the most innovative companies including Canva, On, Asana, Dolby, McDonalds and Nasdaq depend on Culture Amp every day.

Culture Amp is backed by leading venture capital funds and has offices in the US, UK, Germany and Australia. Culture Amp has been recognized as one of the world’s top private cloud companies by Forbes and most innovative companies by Fast Company.

For more information visit cultureamp.com.

How you can help make a better world of work

We're building the analytics foundation for Culture Amp's next generation of workforce insights. This is a hands-on Senior Data Engineer role in our Data Products team, focused on data modelling and analytical query design at scale.

What you'll do

You'll design and build the data models that power insights connecting engagement, performance, hierarchy and retention data. The goal is helping leaders understand not just what's happening in their organisation, but why.

This means:

Building analytical data models in ClickHouse, optimised for complex queries across millions of survey responses and workforce events
Designing schemas and transformations that make it easy to compute insights across multiple data domains
Collaborating with data scientists to bring statistical and ML models into production
Working with streaming data pipelines (Kafka) to ensure data lands in the right shape for analytical workloads

What makes this interesting

This work is central to Culture Amp's product strategy. We have one of the largest workforce datasets in the world: years of engagement surveys, performance cycles, and organisational changes across thousands of companies. The technical challenge is making that data queryable, joinable, and useful for insights that actually matter to customers.

You'll be building something new, not maintaining legacy systems. The insights platform is greenfield work on modern infrastructure (ClickHouse, Kafka, dbt), solving genuinely hard problems around statistical validity at scale and real-time analytics.

You Have

Strong SQL and data modelling skills. You think in sets, understand query performance, and can design schemas that balance flexibility with efficiency.
Strong Python skills for data processing and pipeline development
Experience with analytical databases (ClickHouse, BigQuery, Snowflake, or similar)
Familiarity with streaming data and event-driven architectures
Ability to work closely with data scientists. You don't need to build the models, but you need to understand what they need from the data layer.

Someone who loves collaboration - our teams are cross functional and you’ll be working with other engineers, team leads and product managers to deliver great outcomes together.

Job Title: Lead MLOps Engineer – Imaging & Machine Vision
Ad Text:
About BT Imaging:

BT Imaging is the original inventor and world’s leading manufacturer of luminescence inspection tools for the solar photovoltaic industry. Headquartered in Sydney, Australia, BT Imaging develops and manufactures high-performance photoluminescence imaging systems used by solar cell manufacturers, researchers, and equipment makers worldwide. We combine innovative imaging techniques with industry-leading ML and data analytics capabilities to deliver imaging systems deployed by top-tier solar manufacturers and research institutions around the world to optimize production, improve quality control, and accelerate innovation in solar energy. With a focus on precision engineering, big data analytics, and sustainability, BT Imaging is a fast-growing, technology-driven company at the forefront of enabling the global transition to clean energy.




About the Role 

BT imaging is looking for an experienced MLOps and Image Processing Engineer to join our growing technology leadership team in Sydney.  

This Role will spearhead the development, deployment, and optimization of machine vision algorithms and ML pipelines across BT Imaging’s product suite. You will architect robust infrastructure, work with cross-functional teams, engage with key strategic customers and ensure seamless integration of imaging ML models into production systems. This role blends hands-on engineering with strategic oversight and project management, with opportunities for customer engagement and leadership in a fast-growing sector. Furthermore, working in the Solar Industry offers the chance to make a tangible positive impact on the environment while engaging with cutting-edge technology.  




Key Responsibilities 

·        Lead development and maintenance of scalable and robust architectures for production ML systems and internal ML workflows, including scalable MLOps pipelines for training, testing, deployment, and monitoring of ML models. 

·        Lead development of machine vision ML algorithms for solar cell defect detection, classification, and image enhancement in solar wafer inspection systems. 

·        Lead/oversee project timelines, deliverables, and stakeholder communication for key strategic projects, balancing innovation with on-time execution. 

·        Manage, implement and improve existing ML development workflows from requirements specification through to algorithm development and high-speed code implementation in C++ and/or Rust 

·        Develop and incorporate best practices in CI/CD and on-premise cloud ML workflows, and ensure up to date machine learning models and training pipelines for image pattern recognition tasks, as appropriate. 

·        Collaborate with hardware, software, and scientific teams to integrate high-performance ML models and align with product requirements 

·        Document algorithm structure, system configurations, and usage in internal knowledge base. 

·        Gather bug reports from the field to troubleshoot existing image processing algorithms and pipelines. 

·        Participate in and guide external collaborations for ML development and lead technical reviews, ensuring code quality, reproducibility, and system reliability. 

·        Support software development/deployment efforts and provide assistance with other ad-hoc projects as required 




Essential Qualifications: 

·        7+ years of experience in image processing, computer vision, and/or ML engineering. 

·        Excellent communication and leadership skills with a track record of managing complex technical projects. 

·        Proven expertise in MLOps tools (MLflow, Kubeflow, Airflow, etc.), ML deployment platforms (ONNX, etc) and cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP) 

·        Strong programming skills in Python, C++, and relevant ML/vision/image processing libraries (OpenCV, TensorFlow, PyTorch). 

·        Experience with version control systems, release workflows and code management. 

·        Experience with containerization, orchestration, and CI/CD pipelines. 

·        Experience with project management and team productivity tools (Jira, Confluence). 

·        Familiarity with machine vision and physical imaging systems. 




Desired Qualifications and Experience 

·        Ph.D. or Research Experience in Luminescence Imaging, Photovoltaic Device Physics, Image Machine Learning, Computer Vision, and related fields is a plus 

·        Experience with developing supervised or semi-supervised ML pipelines for image segmentation tasks is highly preferred. 

·        Experience with high performance computation optimization (OpenMP, memory profiling /layout, AVX/SIMD, GPU) is highly preferred 

·        Familiarity with DLL interfacing in industrial software stacks based on Rust and/or LabView is preferred. 

·        Experience of developing and packaging C++ software with Visual Studio is a plus. 




Other Notes: 

·        Candidates must have or be able to qualify for the right to work in Australia. 

·        This is a senior role reporting to upper management and requires regular interaction with office-based teams. Hence, this is a fully office-based role and NOT a remote work role. 




How To Apply 

Please send your Cover letter and CV to hr@btimaging.com

Our client is expanding their data engineering practice and is looking for a Senior Data Engineer to design, build, and deliver modern data platforms. This is a hands-on role where you’ll code daily, while also leading small project squads; you'll be shaping scope, running stand-ups, managing risks, and ensuring business value is delivered with zero surprises.

What you’ll do:

Design and build scalable data models and pipelines on Snowflake and/or Microsoft Fabric (OneLake, Lakehouse, Pipelines, Dataflows Gen2, Semantic Models).
Implement dbt transformations with best practices for modularity, lineage, and CI/CD.
Optimise performance and cost across Snowflake virtual warehouses or Fabric capacities.
Lead delivery: plan iterations, manage scope & risks, run ceremonies, and report progress to stakeholders.
Uphold engineering excellence through code reviews, reusable patterns, and strong governance practices.
What you’ll bring:

5–10+ years of data engineering experience, preferably in consulting or enterprise delivery.
Deep hands-on experience with Snowflake and/or Microsoft Fabric.
Strong SQL, Python, and cloud storage/file format skills (Parquet/Delta/Iceberg).
Experience leading small teams or workstreams, managing sprints, risks, and stakeholder communications.
High attention to detail, excellent communication, and a passion for delivering quality solutions.
Nice to have: Databricks, AWS data stack, Terraform/Bicep, advanced dbt/Coalesce skills, data governance, observability tools, BI/semantic modelling, and presales or project management experience.

If you’re a hands-on Senior Data Engineer ready to take ownership of impactful projects, our client would love to hear from you!

Job Title: Lead Software Engineer (Full Stack), Applied AI
Ad Text:
About MotorPlatform

MotorPlatform is Australia’s fastest-growing B2B automotive marketplace and SaaS platform.

The core platform is built. The next phase is the hard, high-leverage work: scaling product, scaling engineering, and scaling operational excellence, while we shift to being AI-first in how we build and how the platform creates value.

The role

We’re hiring a Senior Full-Stack Engineer to act as Deputy Lead / 2IC in engineering. You’ll be a hands-on builder who can take ownership of major initiatives, lead projects end-to-end, and keep delivery moving with clarity and discipline.

Onsite in Sydney. We want fast feedback loops, high collaboration, and strong product-engineering alignment.

What you’ll be doing (this is a scale role, not a “greenfield” role)

You’ll work on the problems that show up when something is already working and growing fast:

Scale system performance, reliability, and developer velocity as usage expands

Harden security, privacy, observability, and operational runbooks

Build new marketplace capabilities that unlock liquidity, speed, and better dealer outcomes

Reduce friction in critical workflows and improve conversion through product-led engineering

Lead projects that cut across web, mobile, backend, and infrastructure

Improve delivery predictability through planning, coordination, and proactive risk management

Mentor engineers and set the bar for pragmatic, high-quality execution

AI-first: what we expect from you

We’re becoming an AI-first business. That means AI isn’t an experiment on the side—it’s part of the operating system.

You’ll help embed AI into:

Product: smarter workflows, better matching, better quality control, dealer-facing efficiency

Operations: internal tools, automation, knowledge capture, faster support and triage

Engineering: AI-assisted development, testing acceleration, improved reviews, quicker iteration

You’ll partner with our AI/BI team to embed intelligence into the platform and marketplace, including:

Integrating valuation engines into core workflows (pricing, buying, selling, approvals)

Shipping analytics and insights (vehicle acquisition and disposal performance, liquidity signals, margin drivers)

Productionising data/AI services: API contracts, monitoring, quality checks, fallbacks, latency and cost controls

Building internal tools for faster decisions (dashboards, alerts, workflow automation)

You don’t need an ML background. You do need to be comfortable shipping AI-enabled features responsibly and using AI to increase leverage.

Tech stack

Web: React

Mobile: React Native

Backend: PHP (Laravel & Vapor) + Node/TypeScript where it fits

Database: Postgres

Cloud: AWS (EC2, RDS, S3, Lambda)

Delivery: CI/CD, testing, modern development practices

What we’re looking for

Must-haves

Min 6+ years full-stack engineering experience in production

Strong PHP/Laravel (non-negotiable)

Strong React; React Native strongly valued

Strong Postgres fundamentals (schema, migrations, optimisation)

AWS experience (EC2/RDS/S3/Lambda)

Track record leading delivery end-to-end and operating as a senior owner

Highly organised, proactive, and quick to absorb product + industry context

Wants to work onsite in Sydney (Lane Cove)

Nice-to-haves

Marketplace / high-growth SaaS scaling experience

AI-enabled feature delivery (LLM APIs, retrieval/search, automation)

IaC (Terraform/CloudFormation)

Testing frameworks (PHPUnit/Pest, Jest/Mocha)

Why this is a strong next step

The platform is real and growing and your work immediately compounds

You’ll have leadership scope without being removed from building

You’ll help shape how we scale and how we embed AI into the business

You’ll work closely with Product and influence what gets built and why

Location

Sydney (Onsite). Not remote. Not hybrid.




Strictly no recruiters

We're looking for a Senior AI / GenAI Engineer with deep Google Cloud Vertex AI experience to step into a client-facing technical lead role on a high-profile enterprise engagement. This is a 5 months contract to start with.
 
This role is ideal for someone who enjoys solution shaping, GenAI architecture, and trusted-advisor work — without being locked into day-to-day offshore delivery.
 
What You'll Do

What Success Looks Like

Job Title: AI Principal Technical Consultant , AI Delivery Acceleration
Ad Text:
Company Description


It all started in sunny San Diego, California in 2004 when a visionary engineer, Fred Luddy, saw the potential to transform how we work. Fast forward to today — ServiceNow stands as a global market leader, bringing innovative AI-enhanced technology to over 8,100 customers, including 85% of the Fortune 500®. Our intelligent cloud-based platform seamlessly connects people, systems, and processes to empower organizations to find smarter, faster, and better ways to work. But this is just the beginning of our journey. Join us as we pursue our purpose to make the world work better for everyone.

Job Description


The Team

We're on a mission to cut ServiceNow project delivery time in half through the strategic application of AI. Our team builds intelligent tools and solutions—leveraging both the ServiceNow platform and third-party technologies—that amplify the capabilities of our expert services personnel. From internal productivity tools to customer and partner-facing AI products, we're transforming how projects get delivered across the ecosystem.

The Role

The AI Principal Technical Consultant who can bridge deep ServiceNow platform expertise with modern AI capabilities. You'll design, build, and deploy AI-powered solutions that accelerate delivery for our services teams, partners, and customers. This is a hands-on role that combines technical implementation with consulting skills—you'll need to understand real delivery challenges and translate them into practical AI solutions. We're looking for a Principal Technical Consultant who can bridge deep ServiceNow platform expertise with modern AI capabilities. You will design and implement AI systems with NowAssist skills, AI Agents, and Workflow Data Fabric, relying on strong programming abilities across various languages and frameworks. You'll design, build, and deploy AI-powered solutions on the ServiceNow platform and using 3rd party tools. 

What you get to do in this role:

Design and implement AI solutions on the ServiceNow platform
Stay current with emerging AI capabilities and evaluate their applicability to our platform and use cases
Developing solutions specific to user requirements gathered in workshops
Coordinating activities with other developers to ensure that Now Assist and platform functionality is designed to support the overall program objectives
Ensuring that best practices in implementation AI solutions are followed
Evaluating new technologies and 3rd party AI tools for use in the expert services organization
Stay ahead of the ServiceNow platform roadmap, evaluating new AI features as they release and determining how they can accelerate delivery
Develop deep expertise in Now Assist across workflows—understanding its configuration, customization, and optimal use cases for different implementation scenarios

Qualifications


To be successful in this role you have:

Experience in leveraging or critically thinking about how to integrate AI into work processes, decision-making, or problem-solving. This may include using AI-powered tools, automating workflows, analyzing AI-driven insights, or exploring AI's potential impact on the function or industry.
At least 8 years of configuration/development experience for complex, highly capable, solutions
Demonstrated ability to influence and consult (providing options with pros, cons, and risks) in a complex and varied customer environment, while providing thought leadership to customer sponsors/stakeholders in solving business process and/or technical problems
Maintain at least 2 ServiceNow mainline CIS certifications
Maintain ServiceNow Certified Application Developer (CAD) certification
Act as a technical lead on any engagement
Understanding of AI Models, Deep Learning Models, and Large Language Models with a focus on Generative AI.
Experience with ServiceNow’s Predictive/Task Intelligence, AI Search, and Virtual Agent is highly valued.
Experience with development on the ServiceNow platform capabilities (Studio IDE, Mobile, Automated Test Framework, Delegated Development, Flow Designer, Source Control, APIs, and Integrations)
Experience with data management, database design, and database concepts
Knowledge and experience with technical components such as LDAP, VPN, SSL, SAML/SSO and other widespread enterprise technologies
Connect chat, agent chat, and virtual agent configuration and design experience
Encryption understanding and core design principals with customers (Platform, Edge, Database, Full Disk, etc)
Strong Javascript skills with practical experience
Experience with Self Hosted implementations and/or Domain Separation is a plus
Experience with data management, database design, and database concepts
Strong interpersonal skills, customer-centric attitude, and ability to operate within a culturally diverse environment
Proven team builder with the ability to mentor and develop talent
Analytical and problem-solving abilities
A keen eye for detail and the ability to spot and fix errors in complex code
Ability to perform tasks independently
Good presentation and report-writing skills
Up to 30% travel annually

Additional Information


Work Personas

We approach our distributed world of work with flexibility and trust. Work personas (flexible, remote, or required in office) are categories that are assigned to ServiceNow employees depending on the nature of their work and their assigned work location. Learn more here. To determine eligibility for a work persona, ServiceNow may confirm the distance between your primary residence and the closest ServiceNow office using a third-party service.

Equal Opportunity Employer

ServiceNow is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, creed, religion, sex, sexual orientation, national origin or nationality, ancestry, age, disability, gender identity or expression, marital status, veteran status, or any other category protected by law. In addition, all qualified applicants with arrest or conviction records will be considered for employment in accordance with legal requirements. 

Accommodations

We strive to create an accessible and inclusive experience for all candidates. If you require a reasonable accommodation to complete any part of the application process, or are unable to use this online application and need an alternative method to apply, please contact globaltalentss@servicenow.com for assistance. 

Export Control Regulations

For positions requiring access to controlled technology subject to export control regulations, including the U.S. Export Administration Regulations (EAR), ServiceNow may be required to obtain export control approval from government authorities for certain individuals. All employment is contingent upon ServiceNow obtaining any export license or other approval that may be required by relevant export control authorities.

You'll design, build, and deploy AI-powered solutions on the ServiceNow platform and using 3rd party tools. 

What you get to do in this role:

Design and implement AI solutions on the ServiceNow platform
Stay current with emerging AI capabilities and evaluate their applicability to our platform and use cases
Developing solutions specific to user requirements gathered in workshops
Coordinating activities with other developers to ensure that Now Assist and platform functionality is designed to support the overall program objectives
Ensuring that best practices in implementation AI solutions are followed
Evaluating new technologies and 3rd party AI tools for use in the expert services organization
Stay ahead of the ServiceNow platform roadmap, evaluating new AI features as they release and determining how they can accelerate delivery
Develop deep expertise in Now Assist across workflows—understanding its configuration, customization, and optimal use cases for different implementation scenarios

Qualifications


To be successful in this role you have:

Experience in leveraging or critically thinking about how to integrate AI into work processes, decision-making, or problem-solving. This may include using AI-powered tools, automating workflows, analyzing AI-driven insights, or exploring AI's potential impact on the function or industry.
At least 8 years of configuration/development experience for complex, highly capable, solutions
Demonstrated ability to influence and consult (providing options with pros, cons, and risks) in a complex and varied customer environment, while providing thought leadership to customer sponsors/stakeholders in solving business process and/or technical problems
Maintain at least 2 ServiceNow mainline CIS certifications
Maintain ServiceNow Certified Application Developer (CAD) certification
Act as a technical lead on any engagement
Understanding of AI Models, Deep Learning Models, and Large Language Models with a focus on Generative AI.
Experience with ServiceNow’s Predictive/Task Intelligence, AI Search, and Virtual Agent is highly valued.
Experience with development on the ServiceNow platform capabilities (Studio IDE, Mobile, Automated Test Framework, Delegated Development, Flow Designer, Source Control, APIs, and Integrations)
Experience with data management, database design, and database concepts
Knowledge and experience with technical components such as LDAP, VPN, SSL, SAML/SSO and other widespread enterprise technologies
Connect chat, agent chat, and virtual agent configuration and design experience
Encryption understanding and core design principals with customers (Platform, Edge, Database, Full Disk, etc)
Strong Javascript skills with practical experience
Experience with Self Hosted implementations and/or Domain Separation is a plus
Experience with data management, database design, and database concepts
Strong interpersonal skills, customer-centric attitude, and ability to operate within a culturally diverse environment
Proven team builder with the ability to mentor and develop talent
Analytical and problem-solving abilities
A keen eye for detail and the ability to spot and fix errors in complex code
Ability to perform tasks independently
Good presentation and report-writing skills
Up to 30% travel annually

Company description:



Insignia Financial Limited is an Australian financial services company which offers a range of products and services including financial advice, superannuation, investment management and trustee services



Job description:



· Shape the future - Build and scale AI solutions that transform how advice and operations run on our Wrap platform

· Shape the AI capability of one of Australia's leading financial services businesses.

· Make an impact - Build AI capabilities into Wrap and deliver tangible value for clients, advisers, and the business


Are you ready to move beyond AI hype and build solutions that deliver tangible human value?

We are looking for a Senior AI Engineer to help us transform our $100bn Wrap platform into an AI-first ecosystem. This is a rare opportunity to not only deliver high-performance applications but to architect the technical frameworks and robust AI governance that will underpin our entire enterprise capability.

This role offers high visibility across the business, giving you the platform to influence our long-term AI strategy while working in a highly collaborative environment. You'll partner with cross-functional teams to solve a massive variety of 'real-world' financial puzzles—from optimizing advice workflows to scaling operational intelligence. If you are looking for a role that balances cutting-edge engineering with the chance to lead responsible innovation at scale, join us and put your fingerprints on the future of financial wellbeing in Australia


What you'll do

· Model Development & Deployment: Build, deploy, and maintain AI-enabled apps and microservices, leveraging enterprise AI platforms, tools, and models.

· Research & Prototyping: Deliver labs, pilots, and proofs of concept to test and scale new ideas.

· Solution Architecture: Shape AI/ML system design and technical decisions for the Wrap platform.

· Collaboration & Leadership: Partner with engineers, product managers, and data scientists while mentoring junior team members.

· Data Handling: Work across relational, NoSQL, vector, and cloud-based databases to enable retrieval, search, and processing in AI-powered solutions.

· Performance & Ethics: Ensure models are scalable, reliable, explainable, secure, and ethically deployed.

What You Bring to This Role

· Bachelor's or Master's in Computer Science, AI, Data Science, or related field.

· 3-5+ years' hands-on experience delivering production-ready AI applications at scale.

· Strong experience as a Senior Developer leading delivery and mentoring others.

· Deep technical expertise across:

o AI/ML model development, deployment, RAG, vector databases, Hugging Face/open source libraries

o Languages: Java (incl. Kotlin), Python, JavaScript

o Cloud: AWS, GCP, Azure; containerisation: Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD pipelines

o Databases: relational (Postgres/MySQL), NoSQL (MongoDB, Cassandra), vector (ElasticSearch, VectorPG)

· Strong engineering best practices - version control, clean code, testing, peer reviews.

· A collaborative mindset, problem-solving skills, and the ability to mentor others.

Why join us?

This is more than just an engineering role - it's an opportunity to shape the AI capability of one of Australia's leading financial services businesses.

· Scale & impact - Your work will power efficiencies for advisers, back office, and clients across a $100bn platform.

· Enterprise AI vision - Be part of a business with a clear, governance-first AI strategy, backed by leadership and investment.

· High visibility - influencing how AI is adopted and scaled across the Wrap business.

· Growth & learning - Stay at the forefront of AI/ML engineering, delivering pilots, POCs, and production solutions.

· Ambition & innovation - Join a company moving fast! We're ambitious, we're scaling, and we want AI engineers who thrive in that environment.

Find the better way

What gets us excited about working here? Helping people feel good about their money as one of Australia's leading financial wellbeing organisations. From those starting out to those retiring. As your team, we'll show up for you and together we will create financial wellbeing for every Australian. Because we know people who are confident about their financial future live better lives.

If this sounds like your kind of career, you sound like our kind of person. With us, you'll do work that builds your technical know-how and challenges our entire industry to move forward. Along the way, you'll be free to explore new ideas and technology, solve problems in a team, and independently to get great things done. Around here, we like to call it "putting our fingerprints on the future".

People-inspired tech

Deep expertise combined with creativity can take on the trickiest of problems. Join our team of brilliant minds and mentors as we explore our way to innovation and apply technology in more human ways than ever.

Anduril Industries is a defense technology company with a mission to transform U.S. and allied military capabilities with advanced technology. By bringing the expertise, technology, and business model of the 21st century’s most innovative companies to the defense industry, Anduril is changing how military systems are designed, built and sold. Anduril’s family of systems is powered by Lattice OS, an AI-powered operating system that turns thousands of data streams into a realtime, 3D command and control center. As the world enters an era of strategic competition, Anduril is committed to bringing cutting-edge autonomy, AI, computer vision, sensor fusion, and networking technology to the military in months, not years.

Anduril’s Manufacturing team is seeking a Manufacturing Engineer with an Electronic, Mechatronic or Process Engineering background to join our team in Sydney, Australia. The Manufacturing Team is responsible for rapidly iterating and building cutting-edge defence hardware for undersea and flight vehicles. As a Manufacturing Engineer, you will have responsibility for optimizing Anduril’s manufacturing operations for best-in-class quality, reliability, speed, and asset utilization, all while meeting critical customer and internal development timelines. The Manufacturing Engineer will be instrumental in taking a data-driven approach to designing production workstations and manufacturing processes to meet these objectives. Executing on this responsibility will entail active collaboration with Anduril teams across Supply Chain, Engineering, Quality, and Business Operations.

The right person for this role can demonstrate past ownership on solving operational challenges with creative solutions in a fast-paced, resource-limited environment. This person will be flexible to provide support wherever needed to ensure products are built and tested under stringent quality standards. If you are someone who thrives in such an environment, then this role is for you.

What You'll Do

Design, document and implement efficient manufacturing processes to meet both new product development (NPI) and full-rate production goals through the development of process workflows and detailed work instructions.
Provide technical guidance to the production team as well as act as a liaison between engineering, supply chain and other departments to ensure production success.
Generate controlled MBOMs, work and test instructions that can be easily followed by technician team in MES or other test execution systems.
Define design requirements and implement semi-automated testing equipment/protocols for subsystem characterization and reliability/environmental testing.
Produce and maintain testing logs/data, develop library of issues with troubleshooting logic/diagrams for fast issue resolution.
Perform hands-on and data-driven root cause analysis of electromechanical subsystems utilizing structured problem solving methodologies.
Proactively identify imbalances and bottlenecks caused by line layout, parts shortages, staffing shortages, and other production constraints by understanding cycle time and Quality metrics.
Collaborate with the Quality team to set quality standards, implement inspection processes and analyze product specifications to ensure manufacturing capabilities align with quality requirements.
Foster a collaborative environment that encourages knowledge sharing and team engagement.
Adhere to all health and safety regulations, promoting a culture of safety within the manufacturing environment.


Required Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Electro-Mechanical, Mechatronics, Electrical Engineering, or related field
3+ years experience in a manufacturing environment where complex electrical assemblies were built.
Solid understanding of hardware manufacturing processes for electronics (PCBAs, sensor hardware, battery power systems, cable harnesses etc.) and electromechanical systems.
Familiarity with hardware testing and automated test systems (LabVIEW, Test Stand, etc.), programming languages such as Python, Matlab, SHELL, and computer hardware communication protocols: USB, Ethernet, RS232, RS485, PCIe, HDMI, CAN, etc
Strong technical ability to read technical documentation such as electrical schematic drawings, 3D CAD files
Have experience with programming/testing a wide range of sensors, actuators, and electrical components
Demonstrated ability to own a product in manufacturing from start to finish; coordinating among multiple internal and external parties to achieve on-time deliveries under stringent quality standards
Prior knowledge and interaction with a Manufacturing Execution System (MES) for production operations
Prior knowledge of Oracle or a similar Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) system
Ability to obtain and maintain an Australian Government Security Clearance


Preferred Qualifications

Production line design and set up - Value Stream mapping, material flow lines, one piece flow, workstation design
Experience with CAD and production simulation software (NX/Solidworks)
Experience with Teamcenter PLM
Knowledge of Lean Manufacturing principles / implementation
